It was a mid winters mourn, where the crisp cold air slowly froze the water into lovely icicles, and froze the grass stiff. A cold fog had taken the morning and was as thick as a pot of stew. I birds where long gone south by this time, and only the sounds of the alarm clocks were on the winter wind.
     A young man appeared, forcing the fog to bow around him as if he controlled the fog itself. Down the street, the icy air did not penetrate his black duster and black leather gloves.  A hat of black leather covered  his brow and a black bandanna covered his mouth. A strange outfit for a man in this day and age.
     Through the fog another figure broke the creamy air, this time a woman. Her long golden flowing hair and full lush lips that would drive the strongest man to insanity. She wore a red leather cloak, with red leather gloves. She wore red lens glasses, and long red leather boots. She was truly a beauty of woman.
     The man knew who she was from her aura and drew his black sword from its hold hidden under his duster. The blade was a magnificent black with red trim, the leather of the dreaded black dragon wrapping the handle. The eye's of the stranger in black where as white as snow. Clearly this man was the cause of the fog which blinded all others. The beauty in red blew into her fist and arose a flaming sword, that which is wielded by a master flame summoner. She removed her glasses and the light of the flames burned the fog from her face, the battle was about to begin.
     The man in black took the monster sword and swung, splitting the fog with a loud whooshing sound. The lady met his blade and parried. The flaming sword seem to bounce of the black duster like a stone on a pond. Whom ever the man was he was old, and powerful. Again the man attacked, this time meeting the woman's sword, knocking her back about five yards. She opened her mind and let the flames flow into her hand, enhancing the swords power. She knew that if she was to hurt stranger, she needed all her strength. The man struck one last time, making it clear he wanted to end this battle before anyone would notice the two on this cold morning. The black blade dug deep into the woman's frame, blood pouring buckets full it seems onto the frozen street. The flames in her hand disappeared, and her life seemed to be fading as well. The man in black took a silk clothe and squeezed the red liquid from his dark blade, cleaning it as a master swordsman was known to do. But unlike others of his kind, he took the tainted parcel and placed it over the woman's face. "Your end has not yet arrived" the man whispered into her ear. The flames of his words and her soul mended the wound which the brutal attack caused. The beauty's eyes seemed to brighten as she focused onto the strangers face. She removed the bandanna, and her eye's focused onto her old friends face. "Sean, by the force of your attacks, I was wondering if it was you. I knew you were after the dark blade, but wasn't sure if you had found it!" she said now having full strength back. "well Angela, you finally mastered the art of the flame. I'm glad your hard work has paid off. Do you have news of Andre and Joel? have they developed as much as you?" Sean said, focusing his Ice powers to thicken the fog round them so as non could spy on them. "Joel has mastered the powers of wind, and Andre, Andre has found a way to bend the very rocks from the earth to his bidding. They will be formidable opponents indeed". Sean grabbed some black glasses from inside his coat. "Whom will you be fighting next sean?" a spark of curiosity in her voice. "I think my next target will be Maria. I heard she too has taken up the sword, and her healing powers my prove to be a challenge in beating her" said Sean, who has turned towards the south. Angela watched as he continued his long walk, and his journey to become the best.

Clear moon light coming from the window as it hits the face of an old book. I pull the pages apart as dust falls like snowflakes on a crisp winter mourn. I look only to find a name written, "sean". But I was eager to know more so I turned the page and uncovered the family tree of a person long forgotten. The clarity that was in my head while on a mission was startling even to a buddhist monk. Page after page I flipped wondering who this person was and what he accomplished. Never once did the book ever mention his name. Until Finally I had reached the last page. This was the moment I knew. The last page had only one word on it as well. And that word, was live.

Well hello there. Yes I know its been a while. Seems like every time I get on here I just seem to bitch about something doesn't it. well this time, is no different. Have you ever noticed that when it comes to people its all about appearances. No matter how smart, funny, and interesting the person is, its all about the outside to most people. Lets take me for instance. For you people who know me, I would say I am a really cool guy. Sure I work full-time and I do mean FULL-TIME, but when I can I have no problems helping out a friend. I'll lend you my jacket or even just hold you tight in my arms to warm you up on a cold night, or sit down and have a heart to heart if you ever needed a little insight. I try my best to make the people i care about (friends, family) happy, at the expense of my own happiness. I grew up in a house where my sister tore my family apart with her stupid acts, and constant run in with the police and I was forced to grow up too fast. I have an anger problem but when something makes me mad I swallow it up until I explode and really hurt someone. I try, and give as much as I can and never ask for anything in return. Now fast forward to the present. I have a nice job where I travel, I'm in San Jose california right now. Now its been a LONG time since I last was involved with someone. Every time I try to get to know someone, they shoot me down because of my size. No one wants to take the time to get to know me. If they did they would see that I am a person the same as them who has needs, and feelings just like they do. But alas thats not how society works. I feel trapped and i'm suffocating in this place called "life". I guess I'm going to be one of those people who are going to be alone until the day they died. The only thing that I could say I would have accomplished is the happiness of others. I am almost 22, been single since I was 17, and to tell you the truth, after all that time of being alone one tends to get lonely. I can't give the person I love a call, or be able to just sit and hold onto her. . .thats all I want. . .just. . .

The simple life.





So Everyday is almost the same thing. I wake up in the evening, go to work. I put up with hell from managers that think they know everything till I put them in their place. I return home to try and go back to sleep but I get woken up five to six times a day because people decide to call me when I try and sleep. For almost a month since I moved into my new place this has been the case. There is only one thing that kept me going till the weekend, and that my friends is the hope I can hang out with my friends over the weekend, maybe talk a little bit, have a nice intellectial conversation but alas. . . . not a word. From people I had not seen in almost three years The only thing I get is a few phone calls and see them for an hour at another friends house. The fact I try so hard to stay calm around people is starting to wear thin. I am noticing that I am getting closer and closer to completely loosing it with society. I have not had a relationship with anyone in a long time, All my friends move away and the ones that do stay live far enough away I'd have to make a trip to see them. Why does this so called god like to play these games. He placed poeple on the earth and what happens, humanity felt like they need to break the rules so they get kicked out of paradise and sent to a world where people kill themselves, others, and other people live in fear all the time. That is what kind of world we live in. Its also a lonely place. Full of desperate souls like myself who seek companionship, excitement, and intellectual sttimulation. Listen to me. . . I sound like a 50 year old man when I am only 21. The only thing I can do now is go to sleep and prepair for what happens when I wake in six hours. I plan on turning my phone off today so maybe i'll get a good days rest. . . and maybe tomarrow might be a better and brighter day in my life. . . .maybe. . . .

What can be said about this feeling called love? Well my fellow readers and writers i have this question for you. You meet someone after a long time apart. They seem different to you then they did before. You think nothing of it and go along with your regular life. However, and this is key now, you keep thinking about them. Now lets say this person is in a relationship, what do you do? Do you tell this person how you feel? Or would you rather cherish your relationship and stay in a friendly kind of way? I can see how this is a difficult question to answer. I would personally wait and cherish my friendship first, yes I may have feelings for this person, but i'd rather not lose what we have to chase after a dream which may not come true. What would you say my readers? tell me what you would do I'm dying to know.

I walked alone down a dark path waiting to see a bright light which help a great treasure. Peeking out of the holes of a hot facial mask i could see the other children laughing and looking into their bags and pulling out tiny chocolate treasures which they quickly threw into theirs mouths and devoured. It was my favorite and yet most puzzling time of the year, in which all the children and even some of the adults would get together in the cold streets and move from house to house looking for handouts of candy from their neighbors who would laugh and say "aw how cute" to their little children in costumes of bears, witches, and all types of fantasy beings. The first house i pulled up to was a dark grey house with blue trimming on it. My choice of costume this year was one of those weird intel blue men I saw on the commercial. I was proud with my bag ready to receive what ever sweet, and gooey treat that the person behind the door would give me. "Ding dong" the doorbell went as I slowly moved my finger from the button. The door slowly moved open and out popped a very tall man in a frankenstein outfit. I was a little scared, but nothing would keep me away from my candy. "Trick or Treat" I exclaimed holding my bag out. The man turned back towards the door and not even a second later, he put 4 candy bars in my bag. "Wow" I said as  the fourth one dropped in. The man gave me a huge smile and said "Happy halloween" as I turned away and was off to the next house. The night pushed on and I got so much candy I could tell my dad wasn't looking forward to the dental visit i was going to have to go to after all this. I then arrived at my last house of the evening. The lights were off but i could see a bucket on the front porch. A little sign was sticking out of it. "Take as much as you want" the sign said. I looked inside and saw packages of little jelly beans. I grabbed the bucket and dumped the whole thing into my bag. My dad luckily was looking the other way. We then headed home, which, was going to be the worst night of my life. I sat on the floor of the living room and dumped the goodies i worked all night for. There were snickers, three musketeers, milky ways, mr. good bars, etc. But I decided to pick up my bag of jelly beans first. I opened the package and dumped about nine or ten of them into my mouth. I started to chew when i felt a sharp pain in my jaw. I went to say ow when i accidentally inhaled the glob of jelly beans. The next thing I know was that I couldn't breath. I tried to find my mom but she wasn't downstairs so I grabbed my dad. He say I was suffocating and screamed for my mom to call 911. The last thing I saw that night was my mom and dad trying everything they could to get those jelly beans out of me. That was the night that I died. So the lesson of this story, be careful with what you eat on halloween, cause even a simple little jelly bean can kill you.
